@oofenshmirtz2911 I’m not gonna go try to disprove those strange facts you found even though they seem flawed.

Listen, some men and some woman definitely need to be better humans. There’s other ads and messaging that target both but this Gillette one just happened to target the men. Hopefully the men outraged by this still realize they are the ones who probably need to give their head a shake.

It’s like seeing a commercial/psa about impaired driving that shows people drinking at a party where someone decides to get behind the wheel. Then, because you enjoy having drinks at parties you get outraged because you think they’re assuming the commercial is saying anyone who drinks at a party always decides to drive after. It’s pretty ridiculous to draw that conclusion. But guess what?!? Anyone who drinks and drives after a party needs to be better. That’s all I’m going to reply to you on this.
